The paper deals with the problem of sparse representation of white Gaussian noise, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also uses statistical mechanics (cs.MM) to derive the results. The paper's application to compressed sensing (cs.LG) and its use of the $\ell_{0}$-norm decoding (cs.SI) further support these likely sub-categories.
